race.description: All Too Hard @ Vinery Stud Handicap
race.comment: CALL ME MAGNIFIQUE (4) stepped up quickly from 1800m to 2200m last start at this track and did a fair job to work home into fourth. Lightly raced four-year-old who will harden up following that outing and with the light weight can play a huge role in the outcome. CAPTAIN MAVERICK (1) hasn't won for over 13 months but brings solid staying for to this race. Hit the front a fair way out and just failed to hang on last time out in a similar race to this. Meets a plain field today and with Nash's urgings can go one better. HAMMETT (3) worked home evenly at the end of 1600m here at his most recent appearance. Sparingly raced four-year-old from the Waller camp who looks in need of this sort of journey. Similar story for the stablemate WOUNDER (6) who has raced well all prep over shorter trips. Big chance down in the weights. DANCE DANCE DANCE (5) wasn't good enough in the Port Macquarie Cup last time. Might sneak into the top four.
